ests/**/*.test.ts`)\n\n#### ESLint Config\n- Parser: @typescript-eslint/parser\n- Recommended rules + TypeScript specific\n- Warning on unused variables (unless prefixed with `_`)\n\n### What Needs to Be Implemented\n\n#### Part 1: Toggle Puzzle Solver (`solveToggle`)\nSolves button-toggle puzzles for a machine with N lights and M buttons:\n- **Input**: Machine interface with target light states and button effects\n- **Output**: Array of button indices to press (or null if impossible)\n- **Constraints**:\n  - Each button pressed 0 or 1 times\n  - Must minimize button presses\n  - If tied, return lexicographically smallest solution\n  - Handle up to 40 buttons × 40 lights\n  - Complete in under 5 seconds\n\n**Type signature**:\n```typescript\nfunction solveToggle(machine: Machine): number[] | null;\n\ninterface Machine {\n  target: boolean[];     // desired state for each light\n  buttons: number[][];   // buttons[i] = light indices toggled by button i\n}\n```\n\n#### Part 2: Counter Puzzle Solver (`solveCounter`)\nSolves counter puzzles where buttons increment modular counters:\n- **Input**: Target counter values, button effects, modulus (always prime)\n- **Output**: Array of press counts per button (0 to modulus-1)\n- **Constraints**:\n  - Each button can be pressed 0 to (modulus-1) times\n  - Must minimize total presses\n  - If tied, return lexicographically smallest solution\n  - Handle up to 40 buttons × 40 counters, modulus up to 97\n  - Complete in under 5 seconds\n\n**Type signature**:\n```typescript\nfunction solveCounter(\n  lights: number[],      // target counter values (each 0..modulus-1)\n  buttons: number[][],   // buttons[i] = indices of counters affected\n  modulus: number        // counters wrap at this value (always prime)\n): number[] | null;\n```\n\n### Implementation Path\n\n1. **Create `src/index.ts`** with:\n   - Machine interface definition\n   - `solveToggle` function implementation\n   - `solveCounter` function implementation\n\n2. **Algori